      <text>6.2.20 (Area of circle word problem - garden)</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Janet wants to turf a circular area of her garden. The turf costs £{@cost@} per square metre. If the circular area has a radius of \({@rr@}\)m then what is the total cost? Give your answer to the nearest pound.</p>

<p>Cost = £[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>The circular area can be calculated as \(A = \pi r^2\). Here we have \(r = {@rr@}\) and so the circular area is 
\[
A = \pi r^2 = {@rr@}^2 \pi = {@aa@} \mbox{ square metres}.
\]
Since the cost per square metre is £{@cost@} the total cost is \(£{@ta1@}\) to the nearest pound.
</p>]]></text>
